  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulations:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n- Specific criminal statutes defining money laundering offenses\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Regulatory Agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Securities regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Independent audits\n- Reporting obligations\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
